# English-Speaking Therapist in Brussels

The Brussels practice offers specialist English-speaking psychotherapy for those living and working in Belgium. Expats, EU institution staff, international professionals, diplomats — people who have found that French or Dutch language therapy does not reach the same depth as working in their first language, or who simply need someone who understands both the clinical and the cultural dimensions of their situation.

The work available in Brussels is the same as at the London practices: integrative and Jungian psychotherapy, EMDR, eating disorder treatment, addiction counselling, and coaching for those in professional and leadership roles.

## The Expat Dimension

Living and working internationally creates its own psychological pressures — the loss of habitual support networks, the difficulty of maintaining identity across cultures, the particular stress of EU institutions and international organisations. These are not trivial concerns. They are genuine clinical material, and they are addressed here with the same seriousness as any other presentation.

## Who Comes to Brussels

The Brussels practice serves British, American, Australian and other English-speaking expats, as well as non-native English speakers who work in English and find that therapy in their first language does not serve them as well as they had hoped. It also serves people who have worked with therapists in London and need continuity when they relocate to Brussels.

